[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two in hospital after Carmarthen student accommodation fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two people were taken to hospital following a fire at university halls of residence in Carmarthen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mid and West Fire Service say the blaze was confined to a bedroom at the block belonging to the University of Wales, Trinity Saint David.
Three fire crews and an ambulance attended the scene at 18:25 BST on Thursday.
The pair were taken to Glangwili hospital as a precautionary measure.
